 Ep 613 - Sight Unseen (spoilers)

Ok all us UK stargate obsessives that have sky one will have just seen the new stargate ep - Sight Unseen - but what did everyone think??

Spoiler:
I liked the way the bug things they have in this ep (they live in a parrellel dimension and this device they have lets people see it) - but anyway I like the way they were done, with being a mix between creepy and comic, and very colourful! I thought it was clever as well, the way that to be able to see them, was like a virus rather than the energy thing the machine gave off, it made a nice twist, especially with the renegade guy!

i liked this ep, ok not a brilliant ep but a sit back and just chill out.

jonas seemed much more settled in his role in this ep than any other i've seen this season, really did feel complete. and his acting didnt seem forced, felt a lot more natural than it was say, 6 episodes earlier.

the only thing i'm not liking about this seasons character developments is teal'cs new found sense of humour, sure it's made me laugh but...it's such a drastic change compared to how teal'c used to be.
